1. **Data Partitioning** — The dataset is split across `N` simulated clients to mimic real-world distributed hospital data (with realistic non-IID distribution).
2. **Local Training** — Each client trains a local model on its own data partition.
3. **Federated Aggregation** — A central server aggregates client model weights using FedAvg (weighted average based on local dataset sizes).
4. **Global Model Update** — The aggregated global model is sent back to all clients for the next training round.
5. **Iteration** — Steps 2–4 repeat over multiple communication rounds until convergence.
6. **Evaluation** — Final global model is evaluated on a held-out test set.
